adjectives.description: untired (comparative more untired, superlative most untired)

examples: Contemplant Spirits! ye that hover o'erWith untired gaze the immeasurable fountEbullient with creative Deity!

entries.meaning: Alternative form of untyred (“not fitted with tyres”)
examples: Do not allow untired wheels to remain on the floor of the smith-shop, unless there is a current of air passing under the floor of the shop.
